# Validation Requirements

All code changes must meet the following validation requirements before being considered complete. Use this as a checklist for development tasks.

## Performance Requirements
- Pages must load in under 2 seconds on desktop (4 seconds on 3G)
- GSAP animations must run at 60fps on desktop
- Animations must not cause layout shifts
- Mobile animations must be optimized for performance
- All assets must be properly optimized (images compressed, CSS/JS minified)

## Browser Compatibility
Ensure functionality works across:
- Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge (latest 2 versions)
- Mobile Chrome, Safari, and Samsung Internet (latest 2 versions)

## Accessibility Requirements
- Proper heading structure (h1, h2, etc.)
- Sufficient color contrast (at least 4.5:1 for normal text)
- Keyboard navigation support
- Proper alt text for images
- Form elements with appropriate labels
- ARIA attributes used correctly where needed
- Reduced motion option respected

## Template Validation
Templates must be checked against these criteria:

### Home Page
- Full-screen sections display correctly
- GSAP animations function as expected
- Featured products query returns correct products
- Responsive on all device sizes

### Shop Page
- Products display in a grid layout
- WooCommerce hooks are maintained
- Filtering and sorting function correctly
- Responsive design adapts to all screen sizes

### Product Page
- All product details display correctly
- Gallery and variations function properly
- Add to cart functionality works
- Related products display properly

### Cart Page
- Cart displays products correctly
- Quantity adjustment and removal work
- Totals calculate correctly
- Checkout flow functions properly

## Code Quality
- No PHP warnings or errors
- No console errors in JavaScript
- Proper escaping of outputs
- No deprecated functions
- BEM naming convention followed for CSS
- Responsive design principles applied
- Event listeners properly managed 